<subSubSection id="11E3DCD4FFB7FFDBFF07FD6AFEEEFCDE" pageId="8" pageNumber="277" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="59468F5FFFB7FFDBFF07FD6AFEEEFCDE" blockId="8.[136,787,716,836]" pageId="8" pageNumber="277">
<emphasis id="6B8D534DFFB7FFDBFF07FD6AFCD2FD7E" box="[174,786,716,740]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="277">
Distribution and ecology. – 
<taxonomicName id="9EF9F4DCFFB7FFDBFE48FD6AFCD2FD7E" authorityName="Buerki, Callm., Munzinger &amp; Lowry" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Buerki, Callm., Munzinger &amp; Lowry" baseAuthorityYear="2020" box="[481,786,716,740]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Sapindaceae" genus="Lepidocupania" kingdom="Plantae" order="Sapindales" pageId="8" pageNumber="277" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="guillauminii">Lepidocupania guillauminii</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
is endemic to 
<collectingRegion id="9B3D41BDFFB7FFDBFE8AFD4AFEAFFC9E" box="[291,367,748,772]" country="Micronesia" name="Chuuk" pageId="8" pageNumber="277">Chuuk</collectingRegion>
atoll in the 
<collectingCountry id="21EECFCFFFB7FFDBFE51FD4AFD6DFC9E" box="[504,685,748,772]" name="Micronesia" pageId="8" pageNumber="277">Caroline Islands</collectingCountry>
, where it grows in lowland evergreen forests on volcanic soil and humus (
<bibRefCitation id="3D68F2AEFFB7FFDBFF38FC8AFEE3FCDE" author="ADEMA, F." box="[145,291,812,836]" pageId="8" pageNumber="277" refId="ref11451" refString="ADEMA, F. (1991). Cupaniopsis Radlk. (Sapindaceae): a monograph. Leiden Bot. Ser. 15." type="book" year="1991">ADEMA, 1991</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="11E3DCD4FFB7FFDBFF07FCCBFE30FB9E" pageId="8" pageNumber="277" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="59468F5FFFB7FFDBFF07FCCBFE30FB9E" blockId="8.[136,787,876,1028]" pageId="8" pageNumber="277">
<emphasis id="6B8D534DFFB7FFDBFF07FCCBFF1FFC1E" box="[174,223,877,900]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="277">Note</emphasis>
. – While 
<bibRefCitation id="3D68F2AEFFB7FFDBFEF8FCCAFDE4FC1E" author="ADEMA, F." box="[337,548,876,900]" pageId="8" pageNumber="277" refId="ref11451" refString="ADEMA, F. (1991). Cupaniopsis Radlk. (Sapindaceae): a monograph. Leiden Bot. Ser. 15." type="book" year="1991">ADEMA (1991: 122)</bibRefCitation>
noted that the available material of this species is rather incomplete and that it resembles both 
<taxonomicName id="9EF9F4DCFFB7FFDBFE9AFC0BFE61FC5E" authorityName="Buerki, Callm., Munzinger &amp; Lowry" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Buerki, Callm., Munzinger &amp; Lowry" baseAuthorityYear="2020" box="[307,417,940,964]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Sapindaceae" genus="Lepidocupania" kingdom="Plantae" order="Sapindales" pageId="8" pageNumber="277" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="concolor">
<emphasis id="6B8D534DFFB7FFDBFE9AFC0BFE61FC5E" box="[307,417,940,964]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="277">L. concolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="9EF9F4DCFFB7FFDBFE71FC0BFD97FC5E" authorityName="Buerki, Callm., Munzinger &amp; Lowry" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Buerki, Callm., Munzinger &amp; Lowry" baseAuthorityYear="2020" box="[472,599,941,964]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Sapindaceae" genus="Lepidocupania" kingdom="Plantae" order="Sapindales" pageId="8" pageNumber="277" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="samoensis">
<emphasis id="6B8D534DFFB7FFDBFE71FC0BFD97FC5E" box="[472,599,941,964]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="277">L. samoensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, he recognized it as distinct based on several differences in the amount of indument and in features of the fruits.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
